description.en: Pantheon led by El, with Baal, Anat, Asherah, and others. Forms the religious backdrop for early Israelite theology and later monotheistic reform.
An early alphabetic script developed in the city of Ugarit. Distinct from cuneiform and precursor to later Phoenician script.
Archaeological evidence of small, egalitarian hilltop villages with no pig bones and few luxury items — early markers of Israelite cultural distinctiveness.
Yahweh begins to be worshiped as a supreme or sole deity among the Israelites. Likely emerged from earlier henotheistic practices and polemics against Canaanite religion.
